“What is the Caribbean? is not an unanswerable question. But there isn’t —
will never be — a single, definitive answer that can encompass the
complications of the geographic region named for the Caribs of half a
millennium ago, its history and its culture”: So writes Bahamian blogger
Nicolette Bethel for _[The Caribbean Review of
Books](http://caribbeanreviewofbooks.com/2010/08/11/the-unity-is-submarine/)_
in her review of anthropologist Sidney Mintz's latest offering.

